                 <additions>
                   <list>
                     <item xml:id="a01">
                     <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                     <locus target="#145v"/> Colophon mentioning owner, Gäbrä Haywot and scribe, Wäldä Iyasus
                     </desc>
                     </item>
                     <item xml:id="a02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#146v–147r"/>: mention <persName ref="PRS3500Demetriu"/> (II 1862–70) and <persName ref="PRS2209Athanasi"/> (1869–1876)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#147v"/> mentions Emperor <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> (1868–1913)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a04">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#148v"/>: mentions the name of a scribe, “A good pentrial; the scribe is Ḫabtä Maryam.”
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                     <item xml:id="e01">
                     <desc>
                      Through Psalm 106, the numbers ten <foreign xml:lang="gez">(፲)</foreign> and twelve <foreign xml:lang="gez">(፲፪)</foreign> are in the margins throughout, indicating sections of ten or twelve lines in the text, probably for use with antiphonal readings for morning prayers                     </desc>
                     </item>
                     <item xml:id="e02">
                     <desc>
                     <locus target="#54r"/> the mid-point of the Psalter is marked with the words “Half of David.”
                     </desc>
                     </item>
                     <item xml:id="e03">
                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 3
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                     <item xml:id="e04">
                     <desc>
                       Navigation system: red fabric is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#13 #28 #48 #59 #67 #84 #99 #111"/> yellow fabric sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#7 #20 #35 #72 #96 #105"/>
                     </desc>
                     </item>
                     <item xml:id="e05">
                     <desc>
                       Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                     </desc>
                     </item>
                     <item xml:id="e06">
                     <desc>
                       Scribal intervention:
                       words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#2v #5v #6r #6v #14r"/>, etc.); and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#16v #32r #44v #49r #51r"/> etc.); and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#75r"/> #line 13; <locus target="#85r"/>, line 12; <locus target="#87r"/>, line 16; <locus target="#89v"/>, line 18; <locus target="#101r"/>, line 16); text has been removed (<locus target="#8v #14v #22v #23r #27v"/>, etc.)
                     </desc>
                     </item>
                    </list>
                 </additions>

